title: For Sale:  Who Are These Idiots?
postcontent:
--Trying to sell a gun with out-of-focus pics or no photo at all.
--Just because your AR-15 has optics and an after-market grip does not make it a "custom" rifle.
--Most of us know one Generation of Glock from another, but as a courtesy go ahead and provide that info.
--Most buyers need and want more than just "Winchester 30-30" in the description. Is it an XTR, Ranger, Commemorative? Year of manufacture?
--Why are you asking more for your gun that what I can buy a new one for?
--A Llama 45ACP is not worth $450 no matter what you think.
--Know your AR-15 chambers. Is it .223 Rem, 5.56 NATO, or .223 Wylde?
--A 1, 2, 5, 10, or 20 year old gun is not "new" whether it's been fired or not.
--Just because you built it does not make it worth more.
--Of course we've got pro- and anti-union users of this site, so I'm sure I'll ruffle some feathers with this next one.  I'm going to peg on Colt...
Colt has a union represented by UAW (WFT?) and for about the past 35 years has done nothing but manufacture over-priced sub-standard firearms.  (Do just a little research and learn how they screwed around and lost the M16A2 contract.)  At one time the Rampant Colt truly deserved its premium price and prestige--but those days are long gone.  If you want to dish out over a grand for a run of the mill 1911 that has the Colt name on it, go ahead, it's your money.  If you want a REAL QUALITY 1911 that won't send you to the poor hose, look into the Ruger SR1911CMD.

...and finally...Only an idiot is going to trade away a gun for your junk stereo, dirt bike, laying hens, or tattoo services.

title: For Sale:  Glock GSSF Certificate For Sale
location: Raleigh, Raleigh / Durham / CH, North Carolina
postcontent:
I have a GSSF Glock Certificate that is valid until 2/27/2015. The certificate is exchangeable for any Gen 3 Glock G17-G19-G22-G23-G26-G27-G31-G32-G33. 

You simply take the certificate to your local FFL dealer and he mails it along with a copy of his FFL certificate to Glock. Glock sends the pistol to your FFL dealer and you go pick up your pistol.

There is no charge for shipping and no taxes are due unless you upgrade the certificate. Then, your local sales tax must be added to the upgrade charge ONLY, i.e., you pay taxes on the $35 dollar upgrade ONLY, $35 x .0675 (NC state tax) = $2.36 = $37.36 (total upgrade charge). 

The certificate is upgradeable to the Gen 4 Glocks (same models as previously listed) for an additional charge of $35. 

The certificate can be upgraded the the Gen 3 G37-G38-G39 models (these are the GAP 45 Glocks) for an additional charge of $21.

The certificate can be upgraded for the Gen 3 Glock G20SF-G21SF-G29-G30S-G30SF-G36 for an additional charge of $66.

The certificate can be upgraded to the “Tactical Practical’ competition pistols, the Gen 3 G34 or G35 for an additional $107.

There are other upgrade options, including Gen 4 G34, etc.

I have high resolution (legible) pics of the certificate for those who are interested.

Asking $440. Shipping is available if you cannot pick up.

title: For Sale:  2 AR-15 16" M4 Carbines
postcontent:
I'm the original owner, and both have less than 100rds through them. Great rifles, but I never shoot it as much as my other ARs

Top Rifle: This rifle was put together by Surplus Ammo & Arms in Tacoma, and is an excellent shooter. The upper is SAA with 16" free-floated stainless steel barrel with lightweight profile, and a MI 11" freefloating handguard with rail on top that mates up perfectly with the receiver. The handguard has tapped holes that allow accessories or rail sections to be added easily and securely. The lower receiver is also made by SAA, and I swapped out a ALG QMS nickle plated trigger for the absolute best mil-spec trigger I've ever shot. Other accessories include an extended tactical latch charging handle, MFT Battlelink Minimalist buttstock with QD Sling points, Hogue pistol grip, and receiver endplate with quick attach loop for sling.

**Please note that the Vortex scope is for sale separately

Price WITHOUT Optic: $1200

___________________________________________________

Bottom Rifle: This rifle is a great optics ready carbine. The upper is a Bushmaster factory upper with 16" chrome lined barrel and lightweight profile. It has a fixed mil-spec front sight on it, and I swapped the furniture out for some Magpul furniture and vertical pistol grip. I have a Diamond rear sight that is on at 100yds. The lower is a DPMS lower with mil-spec trigger and some more Magpul furniture including pistol grip with storage, enhanced trigger guard for shooting with gloves, and lightweight 6 position buttstock.

Price: $750 or make an offer

I am not looking for any trades at this time. I do have some 30rd magazines and ammunition that I can sell you if you don't have any - just ask.
